---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Standards"
  description="How we source, review, and update The Yard Scout content. Plain-English commitments to accuracy and operator-honest recommendations."
>
  <section class="container-article py-12 md:py-16">
    <h1 class="font-heading font-extrabold text-4xl md:text-5xl text-slate-deep tracking-tight">
      Editorial standards.
    </h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mt-6">
      <p>
        These are the commitments we hold ourselves to. They exist for trust signalling — but more
        importantly, they exist as a discipline.
      </p>

      <h2>Sourcing</h2>
      <p>
        Every spec, price, and dimension on this site is checked against a primary source. Hot tub
        dimensions come from the manufacturer specification sheet. Sauna heater wattages come from
        the brand's product page. Cold plunge temperature ranges come from the device documentation.
        Pricing comes directly from the seller — never from a third-party reseller blog.
      </p>
      <p>
        If we cite a third-party source (independent test, customer review aggregate), we link it
        directly. If we make a claim we can't source, we don't make the claim.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate recommendations</h2>
      <p>
        Several brands we cover (Plunge, Almost Heaven Saunas, Clearlight, Sun Home, Sunlighten,
        Bestway/SaluSpa via Amazon) operate affiliate programs. We participate in some of them. When
        you click an affiliate link and buy, we may earn a commission at no cost to you.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>The recommendation order on this site is based on what actually fits the use case,
        not commission size.</strong> If a higher-commission product is the right pick, we say so. If
        a lower-commission product is the right pick, we say that. We disclose every commercial
        relationship and we don't gatekeep the reasoning.
      </p>
      <p>
        See our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure">full affiliate disclosure</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Hands-on review caveat</h2>
      <p>
        Where we describe long-term ownership reality (winter behaviour, electrical load,
        chemistry maintenance, install gotchas), we draw on a mix of: hands-on use, manufacturer
        specifications cross-checked against owner forum reports, and independent industry data.
        We will name explicitly when a review is based on hands-on testing vs published-specifications
        synthesis.
      </p>

      <h2>Updates and maintenance</h2>
      <p>
        Every article carries a "Last reviewed" date. Articles covering pricing, model availability,
        and brand line-ups are reviewed quarterly. Cornerstone buying-decision articles are reviewed
        at least once per year.
      </p>
      <p>
        When we materially update an article (changing a recommendation, correcting a spec, adding
        a new brand), we note it at the top of the article.
      </p>

      <h2>What we don't do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No black-hat SEO. No cloaking, doorway pages, link schemes, or article spinning.</li>
        <li>No fake author credentials. We attribute articles to "The Yard Scout team" rather than inventing fictitious experts with fake bios.</li>
        <li>No paid placement disguised as editorial. Every commercial relationship is disclosed.</li>
        <li>No medical claims. We describe what these products are designed to do; we don't tell you they'll cure anything. Talk to your doctor for health advice.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Corrections</h2>
      <p>
        If you find an error, please <a href="/contact">contact us</a>. We'll review, correct, and
        publish a correction note at the top of the article within 5 business days.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
